  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated Emergency Response to Communities Affected by Drought in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Food packs distribution; essential medicines and protein supplements for children; rehabilitation of strategic boreholes; water trucking for one month; de-stocking; seed packs distributions; mass livestock vaccinations.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The program targets the sectors of health and nutrition, water, sanitation, and hygiene, and livelihood support. The program aims to respond to the immediate needs of the drought affected people in North Eastern Kenya and improve their resilience to cope with future humanitarian needs. It works to ensure a consistency of service in basic curative and preventative health services to complement existing nutrition programs. In the WASH sector, it aims to provide immediate and timely support  to pastoralists and refugees  by maintaining and expanding access to lifesaving water and appropriate hygiene and sanitation practices in all target districts. The program will also improve  food security for the target  communities exposed to the impact of climate change in the target areas.</narrative>
  </description>
